n queue is full, handler returns 503 and Retry-After","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes; requires real interaction between handler and queue full-condition mapping to HTTP semantics. REAL-INFRA: external system not strictly required if queue implementation is local persistent component. MOCK-HIDE: mocking 'full' as a simple flag may miss real error-code translation/header behavior. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: none.","test_description":"Fill real queue to capacity, then send another valid webhook; assert `503`, `Retry-After` header present/valid, and no extra enqueue occurred.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.84,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Persistent queue enforces configured capacity and rejects overflow","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes; capacity enforcement is a property of the real queue/storage implementation, not just caller logic. REAL-INFRA: can be validated with local DB/filesystem-backed queue without external systems. MOCK-HIDE: mocking queue capacity would trivially pass and hide storage-level off-by-one/transaction bugs. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: none.","test_description":"Instantiate queue with small configured capacity using real backend; attempt writes up to and beyond limit; assert boundary behavior (accept until limit, reject overflow) and persisted count never exceeds config.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.83,"System":0.14,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
